Mr Danladi Jatau, the minority Leader of the Nasarawa State House of Assembly, has defected from the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP to the ruling All Progressives Congress, APC.  Jatau, representing Kokona West constituency, registered with the APC at his polling unit in Uke-Bassa, Kokona Government Area of the State. While calling on his constituents to embrace the ongoing APC membership registration and revalidation exercise, the lawmaker said he joined APC to support the State Governor in developing the state. “I also joined the APC to contribute my quota to the development of the state and to Nigeria at large. “I want to call on the people of my constituency, who are yet to join the ruling APC to do so in their interest and for the overall development of the state,” NAN quoted him as saying.  Source Dari   -     Former permanent secretary with the Nasarawa State Civil Service Commission, Dr.John Mamman has switched political allegiance from the PDP to APC. At a reception ceremony on Sunday, Mamman, a reputable farmer and also a former school principal, lauded President Muhammadu Buhari’s efforts in giving Nigeria good leadership and… In "Politics" By Awayi Kuje Dari      -        A Chieftain of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Nasarawa State, Mr John Mamman and his supporters have defected to All Progressives Congress (APC) in the state. Mamman, a retired Permanent Secretary, made this known on Sunday at a reception… In "Politics" By Awayi Kuje Lafia - Mr Danladi Jatau, Minority Leader, Nasarawa State House of Assembly, has expressed happiness over the Appeal Court judgment upholding his election, describing it as victory for the people of his constituency. Jatau, a PDP lawmaker representing Kokona West Constituency, made the remarks while speaking with… In "News"